7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"How to Improve OHSMS following ISO 45001 Clause 10"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:30:56+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"How to Improve OHSMS following ISO 45001 Clause 10\n\t\t\t\tWhen reviewing the requirements of ISO 45001 certification in Dubai, UAE to create your"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"How to Improve OHSMS following ISO 45001 Clause 10"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"When reviewing the requirements of ISO 45001 certification in Dubai, UAE to create your Occupational Health & Safety Management System (OH&SMS), many people find clause 10, Improvement, mystifying. It is easy to understand that improvement is important, but the three sub clauses within clause 10 can confuse, even though each sub clause talks about different ways to improve. In this article, you’ll find a simple explanation of this clause, with an overview of each sub clause included."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Clause 10.1 – Overarching"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"This sub clause requires you to find chances to enhance your OH&SMS so that it can achieve its goals. You must next take action to make these changes a reality. It is crucial to remember that details of adopting ISO 45001 in retail industry contains Appendix A to assist you to comprehend the standard when interpreting this and other clauses. Appendix A is split into subsections that correspond to the standard's clauses and explain each one. As a result, Appendix A.10.1 indicates that you must examine the findings of your OH&S performance analysis and assessment, as well as other data, to identify possibilities for improvement that you wish to pursue."}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Clause 10.2 – Incidents, noncompliance, and corrective action"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Clause 10.2 specifies the criteria for a system to take remedial action when an OH&S event, such as an accident or \"near miss,\" happens, or when there is a process nonconformity. This method entails addressing the nonconformity by examining the core cause of systemic problems and then putting measures in place to repair the problem at its source so that it does not occur again. It enables you to verify those process problems that may reoccur are effectively addressed, as well as that risks that may lead to future accidents are addressed within your OH&SMS."}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Appendix A.10.2 provides more guidance on this provision. It is said that certain organizations may have distinct systems for investigating events and dealing with nonconformities. This appendix contains examples of events (such as falls), nonconformities (such as failing to fulfill regulatory standards), and remedial measures (such as removing risks) that pertain to the OH&SMS. It is beneficial to consider these examples while developing your corrective action process and to include them in any material used to explain the process to employees."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16"]}],"$L17"]}]}]
